'This kind of technology, which can read and understand
email, will play a central role in the next roll out of Cortana,
which we are working on now for the fall time frame,' said Eric
Horvitz, managing director of Microsoft Research and a part of
the Einstein project, in an interview at the company's Redmond,
Washington, headquarters.

The plan to put Cortana on machines running software from
rivals such as Apple and Google, as well as the Einstein
project, have not been reported. 

